properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued February 12 at 11:59AM CST until February 13 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...DANGEROUS WIND CHILLS THIS MORNING THROUGH THURSDAY WITH
ACCUMULATING SNOW AND BLOWING SNOW ALONG THE SOUTH SHORE...

.Snow and lake effect snow will impact the South Shore today
through Thursday morning. The greatest snowfall accumulations of 3
to 7 inches are forecast for the northern portions of Ashland and
Iron counties, with lesser amounts of 2 to 5 inches elsewhere.
Blowing snow and dangerous wind chills to 35 below are also
expected.

Bitterly cold wind chills are expected across northeastern
Minnesota and northwestern Wisconsin this afternoon, and tonight
through Thursday morning. Wind chill values as low as -30 will be
possible across northeastern Minnesota this afternoon and evening.
Tonight into Thursday morning, widespread wind chill values
ranging from -20 to -40 are likely away from Lake Superior with
some values approaching -50 near the International Border.

* WHAT...Very cold wind chills expected. Wind chills Wind chills
as low as 30 below zero this evening, and as low as 45 below
zero late tonight and Thursday morning.

* WHERE...Portions of east central, north central and northeast
Minnesota.

* WHEN...From 6 PM this evening to noon CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...The dangerously cold wind chills could cause
frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO NOON CST THURSDAY
